HEADWORD: Bibasic
<hw>Bi*ba"sic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>basic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Having
to hydrogen atoms which can be replaced by positive or basic atoms or
radicals to form salts; -- said of acids. See
<er>Dibasic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
